        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-09T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5017/5–646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-09T18:00:00-04:00">May 9, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>605. Reurtel 835 May 6. Note recently received from Brazilian Embassy states
                    Brazilian Govt through <gloss target="#t_DNC1">DNC</gloss> would place at
                    disposal of US market 400,000 bags coffee per month for 6 months at 3 cents
                    above <pb facs="0530" n="512" xml:id="pg_512"/> present US ceilings in return
                    for elimination of price ceilings. This differs from <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> you received from Minister Vidigal concerning sales of <gloss target="#t_DNC1">DNC</gloss> coffee. Would appreciate your comments this
                    offer.</p>
                <p>Coffee Board Price Committee discussing possible elimination price ceilings with
                        <gloss target="#t_OPA1">OPA</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
